  "text": "In certain situations the analgesic effects of some drugs upon acetic acid-induced writhing can be confused with motor impairment or myorelaxant activities [CITATION_1] . For NOSH-aspirin this is not the case, since it did not cause any alterations in the rota-rod test, which is a classical model to evaluate these unspecific effects [CITATION_2] ). Therefore, the antinociception effects of NOSH-aspirin do not appear to be through peripheral neuromuscular blockade or induction of sedation.",
